<html lang="en" metal:use-macro="main_template">
  <head metal:fill-slot="head" tal:omit-tag>
    <script type="text/javascript" defer="defer">
      <metal:main use-macro="load: embed.txt" />
    </script>
    <title>Hypothesis</title>
  </head>
  <body metal:fill-slot="body" class="dark-noise">
    <div id="home" class="content paper">
      <header>
        <img height="150px" width="150px"
             src="${webassets(request, 'images/hypothelogo_square.png')[0]}" />
        <hgroup>
          <h1>Hypothes<span class="red">.</span>is</h1>
          <h2>The&#160;Internet, peer&#160;reviewed.</h2>
        </hgroup>
      </header>
      <p>Welcome to Hypothesis. For general information about the project, please
        visit the <a href="http://hypothes.is">home page</a> where you can
        reserve a username, sign up for our newsletter or learn how to get
        involved in working to improve Hypothesis.</p>
      <h2>Get Started</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Open the annotation sidebar by clicking on the white tab
          in the upper right corner.</li>
        <li>Enter your login credentials to create your account.</li>
        <li>You can see the annotations on any page by looking at the heatmap on
          the right side of the page. Click on one of the tabs to see the
          annotations on that part of the page.</li>
        <li>Click on an annotation to see it in detail. In the detail view, you
          can see replies that people have left on the annotation. Click the
          "reply" link to leave your own.</li>
        <li>Highlight any piece of text to leave an annotation of your own (try
          annotating these instructions).</li>
        <li>Use this bookmarklet to annotate any page on the Web:
          <metal:main use-macro="load: bookmarklet.pt" /></li>
        <li><a rel="reply-to" href="mailto:list@0.0.0.0">send comments</a></li>
      </ol>
      <h2>Contributing<span class="redtext">.</span></h2>
        <p>Hypothes.is is an open source effort licensed under a 2-Clause <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BSD_licenses">BSD License</a>, sometimes referred to as the "Simplified BSD License" or the "FreeBSD License". Development is coordinated through <a href="https://github.com/hypothesis">our Github repository</a> utilizing the issue tracking and wiki tools provided there. Additionally, we manage a mailing list which you can subscribe to by sending an email to <a href="&#x6d;&#x61;&#x69;&#x6c;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#100;&#101;&#x76;&#x2b;&#x73;&#x75;&#x62;&#115;&#99;&#114;&#105;&#98;&#x65;&#x40;&#x6c;&#x69;&#x73;&#116;&#46;&#104;&#121;&#112;&#x6f;&#x74;&#x68;&#x65;&#x73;&#46;&#105;&#115;">&#100;&#101;&#x76;&#x2b;&#x73;&#x75;&#x62;&#115;&#99;&#114;&#105;&#98;&#x65;&#x40;&#x6c;&#x69;&#x73;&#116;&#46;&#104;&#121;&#112;&#x6f;&#x74;&#x68;&#x65;&#x73;&#46;&#105;&#115;</a> (<a href="http://list.hypothes.is/archive/dev">archive</a>).</p> 

      <h2>Resources</h2>
        <p>Note the <a href="https://github.com/hypothesis/h/wiki">project wiki</a>, including a <a href="http://docs.hypothes.is/roadmap/">roadmap</a>, detailed <a href="https://github.com/hypothesis/h/wiki/_pages">descriptions</a> and <a href="https://github.com/hypothesis/h/wiki/Mockup-index">mockups</a> of upcoming features, and <a href="https://github.com/hypothesis/h/issues">current issues</a> needing development attention. Additionally, our <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/hypothesis-forum" target="_blank">forum</a> is a great place to get answers and offer feedback. After you're done familiarizing yourself with the project landscape we recommend reading our <a href="https://github.com/hypothesis/h/blob/develop/CONTRIBUTING.rst">contributor guide</a> which details our work-flow, conventions and licensing administrivia. Additionally, please feel free to join us in <a href="http://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=hypothes.is">#hypothes.is</a> on <a href="http://freenode.net/">freenode</a> and subscribe to our mailing list.</p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
